01:43.103 --> 01:44.572
Come on.
Everybody ain't Jamal.

01:44.605 --> 01:45.939
(laughs)

01:45.973 --> 01:48.276
But seriously, why don't you...

01:48.309 --> 01:50.678
just do the duet?
Be on the track.

01:50.711 --> 01:52.646
'Cause I'm not an artist;
I'm an amateur,

01:52.680 --> 01:54.282
and you need a real artist
on this song.

01:54.315 --> 01:56.450
I think homeboy just scared.

01:56.484 --> 01:59.086
He about to fall up
in this-this music life.

01:59.119 --> 02:00.521
-He's gonna leave everything
behind. -All right,

02:00.554 --> 02:02.323
-Dr. Freud.
-Don't-don't matter.

02:02.356 --> 02:05.193
-Don't-don't get wrapped up.
Wait, hold up. -(phone chimes)

02:07.628 --> 02:09.430
Y'all stay at it, all right?
That's my mom.

02:09.463 --> 02:11.165
I got to go to Hakeem's
custody hearing, all right?

02:11.199 --> 02:12.866
-All right, baby.
-All right, man.

02:15.236 --> 02:18.339
DR. LAMBERT: I know
patients are often reticent

02:18.372 --> 02:20.040
with new therapists,

02:20.073 --> 02:24.245
but... I can't help you
if you're holding back.

02:26.314 --> 02:28.649
(sighs)

02:28.682 --> 02:30.951
Um...

02:30.984 --> 02:33.221
I, uh...

02:33.254 --> 02:34.988
I started seeing somebody.

02:35.022 --> 02:38.492
A woman. Her name is, um...

02:38.526 --> 02:40.794
Pamela.

02:40.828 --> 02:43.397
That's wonderful.

02:43.431 --> 02:45.633
Yeah, it's wonderful.
She's wonderful, doc.

02:45.666 --> 02:48.402
Only, uh, she's a cop.

02:48.436 --> 02:51.472
NYPD, and my family

02:51.505 --> 02:54.342
has a pretty dicey relationship
with folks in law enforcement,

02:54.375 --> 02:57.245
so that's probably not gonna
work out so well, right?

02:57.278 --> 03:00.848
Do you mistrust her? You-you
think she's working an angle?

03:00.881 --> 03:02.350
I don't, I don't know.

03:02.383 --> 03:03.984
I don't know.
I just, I just...

03:04.017 --> 03:06.019
I just know I can't stop
thinking about her.

03:07.388 --> 03:09.156
I can't stop thinking about her.
(laughs)

03:09.189 --> 03:10.891
And-and, Dr. Lambert,

03:10.924 --> 03:12.693
I-I want to call her.

03:12.726 --> 03:14.161
I want to call her.

03:14.194 --> 03:15.996
Yeah, I want to--
I want to call her.

03:16.029 --> 03:18.366
I want to talk to her.
I need to talk to her, and I...

03:18.399 --> 03:19.867
I don't know if that
makes me foolish.

03:19.900 --> 03:21.369
I don't know if that
makes me crazy. (laughs)

03:21.402 --> 03:23.671
-I don't-- I'm spinning.
-Andre, slow down.

03:23.704 --> 03:25.839
You're moving a mile a minute.

03:25.873 --> 03:29.410
And now I have to cut this short
because I have to get to...

03:29.443 --> 03:32.179
get downtown to my brother's
kid's custody hearing, so...

03:32.212 --> 03:34.214
All right, wait.

03:34.248 --> 03:37.117
I'm going to renew
your prescription,

03:37.150 --> 03:39.987
and you can get this filled
on your way to the courthouse.

03:43.657 --> 03:45.259
Thank you, doc.

03:45.293 --> 03:47.728
This way.

03:47.761 --> 03:49.730
(sighs)

03:49.763 --> 03:52.766
Y'all realize that's an original
Klimt and not a print, right?

03:52.800 --> 03:54.468
Please be careful.

03:54.502 --> 03:57.070
-Little better.
-Okay, thank you, gentlemen.

03:57.104 --> 03:59.907
We got to go to court, okay?
But it's good to see the house

03:59.940 --> 04:02.710
-getting back to itself.
-Yeah.

04:02.743 --> 04:05.313
-Y'all look perfect. Come on.
-He seems...

04:05.346 --> 04:08.048
-Yeah, back to normal.
-So he's back.

04:08.081 --> 04:10.318
-COOKIE: I really hope so.
-Yes, I'm back,

04:10.351 --> 04:12.553
so stop talking about me
like I'm not here.

04:12.586 --> 04:15.155
JUANITA:
Mr. Hakeem?

04:15.188 --> 04:16.624
I'm praying for you.

04:16.657 --> 04:18.459
Thank you, Juanita.

04:21.161 --> 04:23.397
Come on. Out of the way, people.
Come on, back up.

04:23.431 --> 04:26.600
-Stand back. -Move out of the
way. -Let these people breathe.

04:26.634 --> 04:28.902
-Come on, back up. -SHEPHERD:
How you doing, Cookie?

04:28.936 --> 04:31.171
-Hey. -Ignore all this,
and pay attention.

04:31.204 --> 04:33.774
It's gonna get ugly in there.
Don't let it get to you.

04:33.807 --> 04:36.310
I'm telling you, calm and cool
is the way to win this.

04:36.344 --> 04:38.512
Exactly. Today,
we are the royal family,

04:38.546 --> 04:40.481
so everybody,
get your feelings in check.

04:40.514 --> 04:42.616
-Let's go in here and win this
for Bella. -Strictly business.

04:42.650 --> 04:43.851
What's today mean for you,
Hakeem?

04:43.884 --> 04:45.919
Everything.

04:45.953 --> 04:48.288
Come on, boy.

04:48.322 --> 04:50.324
*

04:55.329 --> 04:57.965
WOMAN:
You got this, Hakeem!

05:00.468 --> 05:02.603
ANGELO: Okay, why don't
you step over here?

05:02.636 --> 05:04.338
-I'll catch up with you.
-COOKIE: Angelo.

05:04.372 --> 05:06.974
(sighs)

05:07.007 --> 05:09.677
Your mother and I have put
our differences aside.

05:09.710 --> 05:12.212
I think its time for us to put
an end to this petty feud.

05:12.245 --> 05:14.782
Cookie Lyon.

05:14.815 --> 05:15.983
Peace advocate.

05:16.016 --> 05:17.651
Nice try.

05:17.685 --> 05:19.587
But I'm not my mother.

05:20.888 --> 05:22.656
-Good luck.
-Mm.

05:22.690 --> 05:24.291
Yeah, well, you sure do
have bitch tendencies.

05:24.324 --> 05:25.693
Very classy.

05:25.726 --> 05:27.628
Always.

05:27.661 --> 05:29.663
(sighs)

05:35.035 --> 05:36.737
BAILIFF:
All rise.

05:36.770 --> 05:40.474
District Three family court
is in session.

05:40.508 --> 05:43.343
Honorable Judge Lydia Barnes
presiding.

05:45.112 --> 05:46.880
Please be seated.

05:49.016 --> 05:51.318
All cameras gone. Now.

05:51.351 --> 05:54.087
-(crowd protests)
-(gavel banging)

05:54.121 --> 05:55.255
Cameras out, please.

05:55.288 --> 05:56.857
All right, buddy.

05:56.890 --> 05:59.326
And if anybody brought a sign in
here, I don't want to see it.

05:59.359 --> 06:03.831
First person to give me
a lecture on freedom of speech

06:03.864 --> 06:08.436
can have a free stay in my
"contempt of court" jail cell.

06:08.469 --> 06:12.205
These proceedings
are about the fate of a baby.

06:12.239 --> 06:15.342
Anything less is frivolous.

06:15.375 --> 06:17.210
Preach!

06:17.244 --> 06:20.748
I do not speak hood.

06:20.781 --> 06:21.849
(scattered laughter)

06:21.882 --> 06:23.851
No class.

06:23.884 --> 06:25.352
JUDGE BARNES:
Enough.

06:25.385 --> 06:29.289
I've presided over
thousands of custody cases,

06:29.322 --> 06:31.625
and in my practiced opinion,

06:31.659 --> 06:36.530
very few parents impress me
as being remotely worthy

06:36.564 --> 06:38.599
of raising a child.

06:38.632 --> 06:41.602
Let's let today
change that opinion.

06:41.635 --> 06:43.437
Free Bella Lyon!

06:43.471 --> 06:46.139
You, out.

06:46.173 --> 06:47.441
-All right, you, let's go.
-Hey.

06:47.475 --> 06:49.242
Hey, yo. Get off me, man.

06:49.276 --> 06:50.811
Hey. Let go!

06:50.844 --> 06:53.447
It appears this circus
has lost one clown,

06:53.481 --> 06:54.882
so let's get on with it.

06:54.915 --> 06:56.183
Petitioner?

06:57.417 --> 06:59.319
Mr. Dubois.

06:59.352 --> 07:00.954
My regards to your mother.

07:00.988 --> 07:02.923
-What? -ANGELO: Yes, thank you,
Your Honor.

07:02.956 --> 07:04.958
She's, uh, currently
in Gstaad for the week.

07:04.992 --> 07:06.794
With the Carsons, actually.

07:06.827 --> 07:09.429
Please, proceed, Mr. Dubois.

07:09.463 --> 07:12.633
Your Honor, my client,
Anika Calhoun,

07:12.666 --> 07:16.169
is the natural mother
of Bella Lyon.

07:16.203 --> 07:20.073
She comes from a-a stable
and law-abiding family,

07:20.107 --> 07:24.645
and she's supported
by a very educated,

07:24.678 --> 07:28.816
and a, uh, a loving community.

07:30.217 --> 07:32.753
Now, the baby's father,

07:32.786 --> 07:36.857
Hakeem Lyon,

07:36.890 --> 07:39.259
is an aspiring hip-hop playboy.

07:39.292 --> 07:41.629
B-level, at best.

07:41.662 --> 07:44.598
He's immature, unstable,

07:44.632 --> 07:46.433
hedonistic,

07:46.466 --> 07:48.301
sexually licentious

07:48.335 --> 07:50.370
and is an avid drug abuser.

07:50.403 --> 07:52.873
-(whispers): Lies.
-When is he gonna object?

07:52.906 --> 07:54.875
It's his opening statement.
He can say whatever he wants.

07:54.908 --> 07:56.476
Objections only happen
during testimony.

07:56.510 --> 07:58.946
Now, the Lyons, as a family,

07:58.979 --> 08:04.652
are a group of opportunistic
no-collar criminals masquerading

08:04.685 --> 08:06.987
as a music company,

08:07.020 --> 08:09.356
with Lucious and Cookie Lyon

08:09.389 --> 08:12.325
as the violent,
lawless kingpins.

08:12.359 --> 08:16.363
I like to call them
"hip-hop's Bonnie and Clyde."

08:16.396 --> 08:18.398
I think that's cute.

08:18.431 --> 08:21.068
Your Honor,
it is my client's belief that,

08:21.101 --> 08:23.904
left under Hakeem Lyon's
custody,

08:23.937 --> 08:27.374
this child will either
end up injured,

08:27.407 --> 08:31.411
damaged or dead.

08:31.444 --> 08:33.080
-(gallery murmuring)
-Thank you.

08:33.113 --> 08:35.048
Bring out the blades, bitches,

08:35.082 --> 08:36.584
'cause he coming for blood.

08:40.053 --> 08:43.591
ANIKA: Yes, it is true that
I did not expect a pregnancy,

08:43.624 --> 08:46.594
but when it happened, I...

08:46.627 --> 08:48.729
I realized
it was something I wanted

08:48.762 --> 08:51.064
more than anything
in this world.

08:51.098 --> 08:55.002
Except for Lucious's money,
and Hakeem's ding-a-ling.

08:55.035 --> 08:56.870
When Anika had Bella,
all she did was complain

08:56.904 --> 08:58.438
Bella was cramping her style.

08:58.471 --> 09:00.507
Then she went to jail.

09:00.540 --> 09:02.042
Now Bella don't even know her.

09:02.075 --> 09:03.777
I'm who Bella knows.

09:03.811 --> 09:08.115
Unfortunately, Hakeem does not
know good parenting,

09:08.148 --> 09:11.118
because he's never
had it himself.

09:11.151 --> 09:13.020
Bitch.

09:13.053 --> 09:14.922
Mistakes? Yeah, I made some.

09:14.955 --> 09:16.690
But I never lost her,

09:16.724 --> 09:18.892
dropped her or abandoned her.

09:18.926 --> 09:21.361
You've spent half
of Bella's life in jail.

09:21.394 --> 09:23.631
For what charge?

09:26.566 --> 09:28.769
Murder.
(clears throat)

09:28.802 --> 09:30.070
-(gallery murmuring)
-But it was self-defense,

09:30.103 --> 09:32.439
and the charges were dropped.

09:32.472 --> 09:34.775
You had sex with the son
of the man you were married to.

09:34.808 --> 09:36.276
Your-your own stepson.

09:36.309 --> 09:37.878
ANIKA:
We were not married.

09:37.911 --> 09:39.279
Yet.

09:39.312 --> 09:41.314
And I was just...

09:41.348 --> 09:42.916
-Sleeping together?
-Objection.

09:42.950 --> 09:45.619
-Sustained.
-It is not what it sounds like.

09:45.653 --> 09:47.921
It sounds like you a ho.

09:47.955 --> 09:49.623
I had to take
a paternity test to know

09:49.657 --> 09:50.891
if Bella was my daughter,

09:50.924 --> 09:52.726
my sister
or community property.

09:52.760 --> 09:56.563
-Clap that, bitch!
-JUDGE BARNES: Ms. Lyon,

09:56.596 --> 10:00.233
I've put up with your murmurs
and your not-so sotto voce,

10:00.267 --> 10:02.469
but one more transgression,

10:02.502 --> 10:05.739
and you'll be
under this court, not in it.

10:05.773 --> 10:07.140
Am I clear?

10:07.174 --> 10:09.643
Yes, Your Honor. My apologies.

10:09.677 --> 10:12.179
Accepted.

10:12.212 --> 10:14.948
Five-minute recess.

10:14.982 --> 10:16.483
JAMAL:
Yeah, no.

10:16.516 --> 10:18.118
I love what you did
with the bridge. Just, um,

10:18.151 --> 10:20.453
send me the final mix.
I'll get you notes by tomorrow.

10:20.487 --> 10:23.323
Look, I don't care
what you got to do.

10:23.356 --> 10:25.492
Get the mixes done
before I get back, all right?

10:25.525 --> 10:27.360
I don't care what you have
to reschedule, Becky.

10:27.394 --> 10:29.930
-Just get it done.
-I just got off with J Poppa.

10:29.963 --> 10:32.966
He wants to re-sign with Empire,
if he can get a 20 For 20 slot.

10:33.000 --> 10:34.935
That is brilliant. I'll have
Porsha set up the meeting.

10:34.968 --> 10:36.670
Oh, no. I can
take care of it, Ma.

10:36.704 --> 10:38.672
Me and J Poppa go back
to Gutter Life days.

10:38.706 --> 10:39.707
That's right.

10:39.740 --> 10:40.874
BAILIFF:
Court is reconvened.

10:42.876 --> 10:44.678
Let's go.

10:46.714 --> 10:50.884
Being a father made Hakeem
take life seriously.

10:50.918 --> 10:54.121
I watched my little brother
become a man.

10:54.154 --> 10:57.557
Anika is so kind and thoughtful.

10:57.590 --> 10:59.292
I named my daughter after her.

10:59.326 --> 11:02.395
She's everything
all of us wanted to be.

11:02.429 --> 11:06.033
There's just been
a huge change in Hakeem.

11:06.066 --> 11:09.569
You know, I see him
reading books like,

11:09.602 --> 11:11.739
What to Expect
in the First Six Months.

11:11.772 --> 11:15.242
You know, he's...
he's very dedicated.

11:15.275 --> 11:18.045
My daughter won the good citizen
award in high school.

11:18.078 --> 11:19.880
We raised her right.

11:19.913 --> 11:23.050
Keem's a superstar.

11:23.083 --> 11:25.886
There are always
women after him,

11:25.919 --> 11:28.488
but the one girl that stole

11:28.521 --> 11:32.860
his heart and mind
is little baby Bella.

11:32.893 --> 11:36.029
He changed
his whole life for her.

11:37.898 --> 11:39.532
She's his everything.

11:39.566 --> 11:41.769
-(gallery murmuring)
-SHEPHERD: That's all.

11:41.802 --> 11:44.738
Thank you.

11:44.772 --> 11:46.740
ANGELO:
Uh, how long

11:46.774 --> 11:49.109
have you been living with Hakeem

11:49.142 --> 11:52.880
in his Gramercy Park penthouse?

11:52.913 --> 11:54.714
About five months.

11:54.748 --> 11:57.117
Okay.

11:57.150 --> 11:59.286
